# Instructions to compile: 
create a build dir and compile:
```
cd [dir_to_this_repo]
ln -s ../data . 
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make
```

then you should be able to run the executable (change the path to your src dir):
```
cd ../
./HiggsAnalysis test_mt_allsyst.root 100 mt [dir_to_this_repo]/
```


# running on condor:
in run_higgs_analysis.sh,change these lines to your local path:
```
# Source the setup script
source /data/pku/home/zhiyuanl/CROWN-KIT/init.sh

# Now run your actual program
/data/pku/home/zhiyuanl/CROWN-KIT/test/build/HiggsAnalysis $@
```

And the samples, mass and channel to be run is configured in input_parameters.txt, example:
```
/data/pku/home/zhiyuanl/CROWN-KIT/test/test_mt_allsyst.root 100 mt /data/pku/home/zhiyuanl/CROWN-KIT/test/
```
